## 1. Description

This threat model covers infrastructure as code (Terraform, Pulumi), CI/CD pipelines, deployment automation, cloud resources, and platform services. It addresses risks from misconfiguration, credential exposure, and unauthorized access to production systems.

## 2. Assets

| Asset | Classification | Impact if Compromised |
|-------|----------------|----------------------|
| Cloud provider credentials | Restricted | Critical -- full account takeover |
| Terraform/IaC state | Confidential | High -- resource manipulation, secret exposure |
| CI/CD pipeline secrets | Restricted | Critical -- arbitrary code deployment |
| Production database credentials | Restricted | Critical -- data breach |
| SSH keys, API keys | Restricted | High -- lateral movement |
| Deployment runbooks | Internal | Medium -- operational disruption |

## 3. Data Flow

```
Developer -> Git -> CI Pipeline -> Artifact Registry
                                    |
                                    v
Terraform State <-- Terraform Apply <-- IaC Code
       |
       v
Cloud APIs -> VPC, Compute, Database, Storage
```

### Trust Boundaries

| Boundary | Description | Controls |
|----------|-------------|----------|
| Git to CI | Code and config enter pipeline | Branch protection, signed commits |
| CI to Cloud | Pipeline deploys infrastructure | OIDC, short-lived credentials |
| State backend | Terraform state storage | Encryption, access control, locking |
| Cloud API | Provider API calls | IAM, network restrictions |

## 4. Threat Actors

| Actor | Capability | Motivation | Likelihood |
|-------|------------|------------|------------|
| External Attacker | Exploit public services, phishing | Data theft, ransomware | Medium |
| Compromised Dependency | Supply chain, malicious package | Backdoor, credential theft | Low |
| Insider (malicious) | Legitimate access | Sabotage, data exfiltration | Low |
| Insider (negligent) | Legitimate access | Accidental exposure, misconfig | Medium |
