## 5. STRIDE Analysis

### Spoofing

| Threat | Description | Mitigation |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Impersonate CI pipeline | Attacker deploys malicious code via forged pipeline | OIDC for cloud auth, no long-lived keys |
| Impersonate developer | Push malicious IaC or code | Branch protection, required reviews, signed commits |
| Impersonate service | Attacker presents as internal service | mTLS, service mesh, network policy |

### Tampering

| Threat | Description | Mitigation |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Modify IaC in transit | Alter Terraform or config before apply | Signed commits, artifact integrity |
| Modify state file | Corrupt or inject resources in state | State encryption, versioning, access control |
| Modify pipeline | Inject malicious step in CI | Pipeline as code, restricted edits |
| Modify deployed config | Change running infrastructure | Immutable infrastructure, config in version control |

### Repudiation

| Threat | Description | Mitigation |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Deny deployment action | "I did not run that apply" | Audit logs, pipeline history, state versioning |
| Deny config change | "State was changed by someone else" | State locking, audit trail, RBAC |

### Information Disclosure

| Threat | Description | Mitigation |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| State file contains secrets | State output or variable exposes secret | Sensitive outputs, no secrets in state |
| Pipeline logs leak secrets | Credentials in build logs | Mask secrets, use secret references |
| Overly permissive IAM | Role has more access than needed | Least privilege, periodic review |
| Unencrypted state | State at rest is readable | S3 SSE, GCS KMS |

### Denial of Service

| Threat | Description | Mitigation |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| State lock exhaustion | Malicious or stuck lock blocks applies | Lock timeout, manual override process |
| Resource exhaustion | Runaway pipeline or Terraform creates excess resources | Quotas, budget alerts, approval gates |
| Pipeline abuse | Excessive builds consume capacity | Rate limits, concurrency limits |
| Delete critical resources | Accidental or malicious destroy | prevent_destroy, backup, approval |

### Elevation of Privilege

| Threat | Description | Mitigation |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| CI role escalates in cloud | Pipeline gains excessive permissions | Minimal IAM for CI, scoped to deployment |
| Developer gains prod access | Dev credentials work in prod | Environment separation, no shared creds |
| Container escape | Compromised container accesses host | Read-only root, no privileged, seccomp |

## 6. Network Segmentation

| Segment | Purpose | Access |
|--------|---------|--------|
| Management | CI runners, admin tools | Restricted, VPN or bastion |
| Application | Production workloads | East-west restricted |
| Data | Databases, storage | Application segment only |
| Public | Load balancers, ingress | Internet, WAF |

### Segmentation Checklist

- [ ] CI runners in isolated network
- [ ] No direct internet from production workloads
- [ ] Database not publicly routable
- [ ] VPC peering or transit limited to required paths

## 7. Access Control

### Principle of Least Privilege

| Role | Access |
|------|--------|
| Developer | Dev environment, read-only prod metadata |
| CI pipeline | Deploy to target environment, no state read in prod |
| Platform admin | Full access, MFA required |
| On-call | Read prod, limited write (restart, rollback) |

### Access Control Checklist

- [ ] RBAC for all cloud resources
- [ ] MFA for production access
- [ ] No shared accounts
- [ ] Access reviewed quarterly
- [ ] Break-glass procedure documented

## 8. Security Controls

### Existing Controls

| Control | Type | Effectiveness |
|---------|------|--------------|
| State encryption | Preventive | High |
| Branch protection | Preventive | Medium |
| Pipeline approval gates | Preventive | Medium |
| Audit logging | Detective | High |

### Required Controls

| Control | Priority | Status |
|---------|----------|--------|
| OIDC for CI (no static keys) | P1 | Pending |
| State access restricted to CI only | P1 | Pending |
| Secrets in external store (Vault, etc.) | P1 | Pending |
| prevent_destroy on critical resources | P2 | Pending |
| Automated drift and policy checks | P2 | Pending |
| Quarterly access review | P2 | Pending |

## 9. Residual Risk

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|------------|--------|------------|
| Zero-day in cloud provider | Very Low | Critical | Accept -- monitor advisories |
| Compromised container image | Low | High | Image scanning, signed images |
| Insider with prod access | Low | Critical | Further mitigate -- least privilege, audit |
| Accidental mass delete | Low | Critical | prevent_destroy, backup, approval |

